				Age Calculator — Everything You Need to Know
			</h2>

			<div class="space-y-8 text-body text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">

				<!-- Section 1: What Is an Age Calculator? -->
				<section>
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3">What Is an Age Calculator?</h3>
					<p>
						An <strong>age calculator</strong> is a digital tool that determines your exact age based on your date of birth. Rather than offering a rough guess, a precise age calculator computes the full span of time between the moment you were born and the current date — breaking it down into years, months, days, hours, minutes, and even seconds.
					</p>
					<p>
						People use an <strong>online age calculator</strong> for all sorts of reasons. Some need to verify their age for legal documents, insurance forms, or retirement planning. Others are simply curious — wanting to know how many days they have been alive, how their age compares to historical events, or exactly how long until their next birthday. Whatever the reason, an age calculator gives you a quick, accurate answer without any math on your part.
					</p>
					<p>
						The best age calculators account for the irregularities of the calendar. Months do not all have the same number of days. February has 28 days in most years but 29 in leap years. An age calculator that does not handle these variations will give you a slightly wrong answer. This tool handles all of that automatically, so you get a result you can trust.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 2: How to Calculate Age From Date of Birth -->
				<section>
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3">How to Calculate Age From Date of Birth</h3>
					<p>
						Learning how to <strong>calculate age from date of birth</strong> is straightforward with the right tool. Here is the process:
					</p>
					<ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 mt-3 pl-2">
						<li><strong>Enter your birth date</strong> — Use the date picker to select the year, month, and day you were born.</li>
						<li><strong>Optionally enter your birth time</strong> — If you know the time you were born, add it for second-level precision.</li>
						<li><strong>Click Calculate Age</strong> — The tool instantly computes and displays your exact age.</li>
						<li><strong>Review your results</strong> — Your age appears in years, months, days, hours, minutes, and seconds, updating in real time.</li>
					</ol>
					<p>
						This method of <strong>calculating age from DOB</strong> is the most reliable approach because it uses the actual calendar — accounting for month-length variations, leap years, and timezone rules. You do not need to remember how many days are in each month or whether a given year was a leap year. The calculator handles all of that behind the scenes.
					</p>
					<p>
						For people who prefer a quick answer without any setup, simply open the calculator, pick your birth date, and get your result in under a second. The <strong>how old am I calculator</strong> is designed for exactly that kind of instant, no-fuss experience.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 3: Age Calculator by DOB -->
				<section>
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Age Calculator by DOB</h3>
					<p>
						An <strong>age calculator by DOB</strong> (date of birth) is the most common way people look up their age online. DOB is the standard abbreviation for "date of birth," and it is the single piece of information the calculator needs to give you a complete age breakdown.
					</p>
					<p>
						When you use an <strong>age calculator by date of birth</strong>, you simply enter the date you were born and the tool does the rest. It subtracts your birth date from today's date, then adjusts for the differences in month lengths and leap years. The result is your exact age — not an approximation, but a precise measurement.
					</p>
					<p>
						This is particularly useful when you need to <strong>calculate age from DOB</strong> for official purposes. Many forms, applications, and administrative processes require your exact age or date-of-birth verification. An online age calculator gives you that information instantly, without the need for manual date arithmetic.
					</p>
					<p>
						Whether you call it an <strong>age calculator by DOB</strong>, an <strong>age calculator from DOB</strong>, or simply an <strong>online age calculator</strong>, the function is the same: enter your birth date, get your precise age. This tool makes the process fast, accurate, and completely private.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Section 4: Chronological Age Calculator -->
				<section>
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mb-3">Chronological Age Calculator</h3>
					<p>
						A <strong>chronological age calculator</strong> measures the exact amount of time that has passed since your date of birth. Chronological age is the most commonly understood definition of "age" — it is the number that appears on your driver's license, passport, and birth certificate.
					</p>
					<p>
						This is different from biological age, which estimates how old your body is based on health markers, or mental age, which measures cognitive development relative to age group norms. When someone asks "how old are you," they are referring to chronological age — and that is exactly what this <strong>chronological age calculator</strong> provides.
					</p>
					<p>
						Our chronological age calculator expresses your age in multiple time units simultaneously: years, months, days, hours, minutes, and seconds. It updates in real time, so the result always reflects your precise age at this exact moment. This makes it useful for everything from legal age verification to personal curiosity about how much time you have spent on Earth.
					</p>
